dijskstra

public static <V,E extends Graph.Edge<V>> Graphs.ShortestPaths<V> dijskstra(Graph<V,E> g,
                                                                            V source,
                                                                            java.util.Map<E,java.lang.Double> weights)
                                         throws NegativeEdgeException
Single source shortest path using Dijskstra's algorithm to find the shortest path. The weights of the edges must be non negative.

Parameters:
g - graph
source - source vertex
weights - for each edge of g, distance between the origin and the target of the edge. The weights must be not negative.
Returns:
instance of ShortestPaths containing for each vertex its predecessor on a shortest path from the source and the length of this shortest path.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the keys of the map containing the weights is not equal to the set of edges of the graph g or if a value in the map is negative.
NegativeEdgeException
